aka: virtual terminal (VT)

A *virtual console* is a full-screen terminal display on the system video monitor.

Virtual consoles are named → Linux/fhs/dev/ttyN[`/dev/ttyN`] (`N` being a number).
-
The start with the number 1: `/dev/tty1`, `/dev/tty0` represents the current virtual console.

rem {
On architectures where the frame buffer device (`→ Linux/fhs/dev/fbN`)
rem }
